{
  "text": "To investigate whether cells representing phenotypes with more osteoblast-like characteristics than \u03e9 / \u03e9 LDA11 cells express different receptors, we examined cytokine responsiveness in two other murine cell lines, MBA13.2 and MC3T3-E1. MBA13.2 cells have several phenotypic characteristics of osteoblastic cells, including expression of type I and type IV collagen, as well as PTH receptors [CITATION_1] . MC3T3-E1 cells represent a differentiated osteoblastic phenotype, as evidenced by the fact that they are able to secrete and mineralize matrix [CITATION_2] . As shown in Fig. 4 A , MBA13.2 cells did not respond to IL-6, but they responded to IL-6 in the presence of sIL-6R. These cells also responded to IL-11, with tyrosine phosphorylation of gp130 homodimers. Unlike \u03e9 / \u03e9 LDA.11 cells, MBA13.2 cells responded to LIF, CNTF \u03e9 sCNTFR \u2423 (but not to CNTF alone), and OSM, with the phosphorylation of gp130 and LIFR \u2424, indicating that in difference to \u03e9/\u03e9LDA11, MBA13.2 cells express LIFR\u2424.",
  "citation_candidates": [
